{
  "texts": [
    "For instance, if the original text reads \"The driver was injured,\" the extract \"The driver\" is a correct answer to the question \"Was someone injured?",
    "\"; however, it is too short to detect the presence of an injury from the extract.",
    "There are situations with no or only few labelled data.",
    "For a hands-on guide we refer to Chapter 9 of Tunstall et al. (2022).",
    "Here, we briefly demonstrate an approach that is suited for such situations."
  ]
}